{"timestamp":1774455449204,"source_app":"agentic-harness","session_id":"1cfa41c9-b353-48a4-8432-cbe180c7a113","hook_event_type":"PreToolUse","tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01AjYQk7EvcbSrnW9biBcUC3","payload":{"session_id":"1cfa41c9-b353-48a4-8432-cbe180c7a113","transcript_path":"/Users/auto/.claude/projects/-Users-auto-agentic-harness-apps-mas-trees-cda005da/1cfa41c9-b353-48a4-8432-cbe180c7a113.jsonl","cwd":"/Users/auto/agentic-harness/apps/mas/trees/cda005da","permission_mode":"bypassPermissions","hook_event_name":"PreToolUse","tool_name":"Write","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/auto/agentic-harness/apps/mas/trees/cda005da/specs/issue-cda005da-adw-6c946274-sdlc_planner-countdown-variant-merch-badge.md","content":"# Plan: Add countdown variant to merch-badge for promo urgency\n\n## Task Description\nAdd a `variant=\"countdown\"` to the existing `merch-badge` LitElement web component. When this variant is set, the badge reads a promotion end date (passed via an `end-date` attribute) and renders an urgency message based on how much time remains. If the promotion has expired, is more than 7 days away, or has no valid end date, the badge renders nothing. The implementation must follow existing badge patterns, use no new dependencies, and support localization via data attributes.\n\n## Relevant Files\n\n- `web-components/src/merch-badge.js` \u2014 **edit**: add `endDate` property, countdown computation helper, and conditional render logic for `variant=\"countdown\"`\n- `web-components/src/hydrate.js` \u2014 **edit**: in `processBadge` and `processTrialBadge`, when `fields.variant === 'countdown'`, pass `end-date` attribute from promotion data when constructing the `merch-badge` HTML string\n- `web-components/src/price/utilities.js` \u2014 **read-only**: reuse `isPromotionActive` logic pattern; no changes needed\n- `web-components/test/merch-badge.test.js` \u2014 **create**: unit tests for countdown formatting logic and render edge cases\n\n## Step by Step Tasks\n\n### 1. Add `endDate` property to `MerchBadge`\n- In `merch-badge.js`, add `endDate: { type: String, attribute: 'end-date' }` to `static properties`\n- Initialize `this.endDate = ''` in `constructor()`\n\n### 2. Add countdown text computation helper\n- Add a module-level function `getCountdownText(endDateStr, labels)` that:\n  - Returns `null` if `endDateStr` is falsy or unparseable\n  - Parses `endDateStr` via `new Date(endDateStr)`; returns `null` if invalid (`isNaN`)\n  - Computes `msRemaining = endDate - Date.now()`\n  - Returns `null` if `msRemaining <= 0` (expired)\n  - Computes `daysRemaining = Math.ceil(msRemaining / 86400000)`\n  - Returns `null` if `daysRemaining > 7` (too far ahead)\n  - Returns `labels.today` if `daysRemaining < 1` (less than 24 hours, i.e. `msRemaining < 86400000`)\n  - Returns `labels.tomorrow` if `daysRemaining === 1`\n  - Returns `labels.days.replace('{n}', daysRemaining)` for 2\u20137 days\n- The `labels` object defaults: `{ today: 'Offer ends today', tomorrow: 'Offer ends tomorrow', days: 'Offer ends in {n} days' }`\n- Accept override labels from dataset attributes: `data-label-today`, `data-label-tomorrow`, `data-label-days` on the host element (read in `render()` via `this.dataset`)\n\n### 3. Update `render()` in `MerchBadge` for countdown variant\n- At the top of `render()`, when `this.variant === 'countdown'`:\n  - Build `labels` from `this.dataset` overrides merged over defaults\n  - Call `getCountdownText(this.endDate, labels)`\n  - If result is `null`, `return nothing` (import `nothing` is already imported)\n  - Otherwise render: `html\\`<div class=\"badge\">${renderIcon(this.icon)}<slot>${countdownText}</slot></div>\\``\n- All other variants fall through to the existing `render()` path unchanged\n\n### 4. Add default orange color scheme for countdown in `connectedCallback`\n- After the existing style property setup in `connectedCallback()`, add a block:\n  ```js\n  if (this.variant === 'countdown') {\n      if (!this.backgroundColor) {\n          this.style.setProperty('--merch-badge-background-color', 'var(--spectrum-orange-500, #E68619)');\n      }\n      if (!this.color) {\n          this.style.setProperty('--merch-badge-color', '#fff');\n      }\n      if (!this.icon) {\n          this.icon = 'sp-icon-clock';\n      }\n  }\n  ```\n- This mirrors how existing variants handle defaults without introducing new branches elsewhere\n\n### 5. Update `hydrate.js` `processBadge` to pass `end-date` for countdown\n- In `processBadge`, inside the block where `fields.badge` is plain text (not already `<merch-badge`), check if `fields.variant === 'countdown'`\n- If so, include `end-date=\"${fields.badgeEndDate || ''}\"` in the generated `<merch-badge ...>` string\n- `fields.badgeEndDate` is sourced from the AEM fragment field (same pipeline that populates `fields.badge`); no new hydration logic is needed beyond reading the field\n\n### 6. Create unit tests\n- Create `web-components/test/merch-badge.test.js`\n- Test `getCountdownText` directly (export it for testing) with scenarios:\n  - `null` / undefined endDate \u2192 returns null\n  - Invalid date string \u2192 returns null\n  - Expired date (past) \u2192 returns null\n  - 8+ days out \u2192 returns null\n  - 7 days \u2192 returns \"Offer ends in 7 days\"\n  - 2 days \u2192 returns \"Offer ends in 2 days\"\n  - 1 day \u2192 returns \"Offer ends tomorrow\"\n  - < 24 hours \u2192 returns \"Offer ends today\"\n  - Custom labels via overrides\n- Validate `node --check` passes on the file\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- `variant=\"countdown\"` renders the correct urgency text for 1\u20137 days remaining\n- Badge renders nothing for expired, >7 days, or missing/invalid `end-date`\n- Default orange background and clock icon apply when no explicit color/icon is set\n- All other badge variants are unaffected\n- Countdown text is overridable via `data-label-today`, `data-label-tomorrow`, `data-label-days` attributes\n- No new npm dependencies are introduced\n- `node --check web-components/src/merch-badge.js` passes\n\n## Validation Commands\n- `node --check web-components/src/merch-badge.js`\n- `node --check web-components/src/hydrate.js`\n- `node --check web-components/test/merch-badge.test.js`\n- `cd web-components && npm test -- --grep \"merch-badge\"` (if test runner available)\n"},"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AjYQk7EvcbSrnW9biBcUC3"}}
